abstract: Tim Cook keeps taking on Facebook, but Facebook’s stock keeps rising.
snippet: Tim Cook keeps taking on Facebook, but Facebook’s stock keeps rising.
lead_paragraph: The ongoing tension between Apple and Facebook flared again this week, causing a dramatic hubbub in the tech industry. I’d argue it was a nothing burger. Not because it was unimportant, but because it’s clear that despite persistent evidence that our privacy is being violated, it might not matter.

abstract: The 68-to-23 vote marks the second time in two months that a Republican-led Senate has admonished the president on foreign policy.
snippet: The 68-to-23 vote marks the second time in two months that a Republican-led Senate has admonished the president on foreign policy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate, in a bipartisan rebuke to President Trump’s foreign policy, voted overwhelmingly to advance legislation drafted by the majority leader to express strong opposition to the president’s withdrawal of United States military forces from Syria and Afghanistan.

headline_main: Senate Rebukes Trump Over Troop Withdrawals From Syria and Afghanistan
headline_print_headline: President Draws Bipartisan Swipe From the Senate

abstract: A group of moderate Democrats, led by Joseph R. Biden and Michael Bloomberg, are thinking of challenging Trump. If too many centrists run, they could box each other out.
snippet: A group of moderate Democrats, led by Joseph R. Biden and Michael Bloomberg, are thinking of challenging Trump. If too many centrists run, they could box each other out.
lead_paragraph: Howard Schultz, the former Starbucks chief executive contemplating an independent run for president, stated it as a plain matter of fact: For someone with his views — a distinctly white-collar blend of conservative fiscal instincts and liberal social values — there is no suitable political party.

abstract: More than two years into his administration, the disconnect between President Trump and the Republican establishment on foreign policy has rarely been as stark.
snippet: More than two years into his administration, the disconnect between President Trump and the Republican establishment on foreign policy has rarely been as stark.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — They think pulling out of Syria and Afghanistan would be a debacle. They think North Korea cannot be trusted. They think the Islamic State is still a threat to America. They think Russia is bad and NATO is good.

abstract: Facebook leadership has a history of lashing out instead of opening up.
snippet: Facebook leadership has a history of lashing out instead of opening up.
lead_paragraph: This month, Mark Zuckerberg announced that his pledge for this new year is to “host a series of public discussions about the future of technology in society.” He added that he intends to “try different formats to keep it interesting,” and we in Britain would like to suggest such an event for him.
